d33208d16cb4e743927b296d00c09cd0305","tid":238917,"uid":33007,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-11T10:41:19.000Z","msg":"你唔明D咩先?或者你想知D咩?"},{"pid":"e62d3cfa5eb6e69d436191aeba57a57f1041a3a1","tid":238917,"uid":96032,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-11T10:47:56.000Z","msg":"我之前又係卡咗係呢到<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n簡單咁講，你唔好理debit credit個字本身嘅意思先<br />\n應該debit/ credit，係視乎個account<br />\n<img src=\"https://img.eservice-hk.net/upload/2017/05/11/183213_d08e01762a7c74a8c4c52722f1758300.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimg.eservice-hk.net%2Fupload%2F2017%2F05%2F11%2F183213_d08e01762a7c74a8c4c52722f1758300.jpg&h=d20ceec7&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n最重要係記住呢張圖。<br />\n當一個assets account (e.g. Cash, Accounts Receivable etc.)增加時，咁就debit咗佢，減少就credit<br />\n例如我畀咗$1000買一部電腦，咁就Cash credit $1000, Equipment debit $1000<br />\n<br />\nLiabilities 同 Stockholders' Equity就調轉，liabilities/ SE accounts 增加時credit，減少時debit<br />\n不過留意Expense 同 Dividend係例外，佢地增加係要debit，減少係要credit<br />\n例如今年畀咗$10000落廣告on account，咁就要debit Advertising Expense $10000，同時credit Accounts Payable<br />\n希望幫到你，加油<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"de7b2332d8c563e73f56068709bd3cbd7c4e74c5","tid":238917,"uid":10171,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-11T10:52:52.000Z","msg":"唔使分架<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 一堂個教授已經同我地講debit係左邊credit即係右邊。"}]}